During the G8 Summit in L'Aquila, Italy, President Obama and Japanese Prime Minister Aso discussed various topics. They emphasized the significance of economic stimulus and appropriate regulation to address the global economic crisis. They also talked about North Korea, agreeing on the importance of the full implementation of UNSCR 1874 and the denuclearization of North Korea. Additionally, they discussed climate change and stressed the importance of the upcoming Major Economies Forum meeting and a successful outcome at the Conference of the Parties (COP) meeting in Copenhagen in December.